Second to third centuries A.D.(<rs type="criteria">content</rs>, <rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>)</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance type="found">
                     <rs type="found">Robert assumed that this altar-stele was found with the others seen by Reichel, <ref type="inscription" n="625" target="120015.xml"/>, <ref type="inscription" n="626" target="120013.xml"/>, and <ref type="inscription" n="627" target="120016.xml"/>, all of which were found near the <rs type="monuList">Stadium</rs>; it is also copied by Kubitschek on an endpaper with <ref type="inscription" n="626" target="120013.xml"/> and <ref type="inscription" n="627" target="120016.xml"/>. But the location given by Reichel suggests that it was seen south of the <rs type="monuList">Walls, South (east part)</rs>, and should probably therefore be associated with <ref type="inscription" n="629" target="120621.xml"/>, <ref type="inscription" n="630" target="120622.xml"/>, and <ref type="inscription" n="631" target="120615.xml"/>, all found reused in that part of the city wall</rs>
                  </provenance>
